properties.LabelText: Although renamed as a result of better taxonomic understanding, this collection comes from the locality of Tsomo in rural Eastern Cape, the place that gave the original variety name of Stapelia hirsuta var. tsomoensis.
Collector identified specimens as Gloriosa superba. Was noted on label that it was collected at Kei Mouth.
This is an unusually attractive well coloured and showy form of this very variable species.

This tree (1955-4/1) was planted by Stellenbosch Magistrate and tree enthusiast Hannes Loots to commemorate the birth of his first son Hannes Loots on 17 January 1955. The Metasequoia over the pathway was planted to commemorate his second son, Frans Loot
